BMO Capital Markets Hires Decker, Raff for U.S. Real Estate

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-09-13T13:31:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/bmo-capital-markets-hires-decker-raff-for-u-s-real-estate.html
BMO Capital Markets hired Mark
Decker and four other bankers to expand its U.S. real estate
investment and corporate-banking business.  Decker, who was previously co-head of real estate
investment banking at Morgan Keegan & Co., was hired as managing
director and group head, based in Chicago, the Toronto-based
firm said today in an e-mailed statement.  BMO Capital Markets also hired Mark Decker Jr. as a
managing director, David Raff as a vice president and two junior
bankers for the real-estate business, all based in  Washington .  BMO Capital Markets is the investment-banking unit of  Bank
